The paper proposes a new framework that explains cluster assignments in terms of input features, which suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of neural networks as a basis for the framework also points towards the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as the most likely. However, the paper also mentions natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) as potential applications of the proposed method, which makes these sub-categories likely as well. Finally, the paper emphasizes the ability of the method to extract novel insights from data, which suggests a possible fit with the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
